  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Roast the garlic </strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7.</p>\r\n<p>Cut a piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> (or baking paper) approx. the size of an A4 sheet of paper. Add the <strong>garlic cloves</strong> (skins on) to the foil with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Scrunch the edges of the <strong>foil</strong> together to form a sealed parcel and add the parcel to a baking tray.<br /><br />Put the tray in the oven for an initial 5 minutes.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1465.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1465.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1465.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1465.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1465.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Make the hazelnut crumb</strong></p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle.</p>\r\n<p>Zest 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Bash the <strong>hazelnuts</strong>&nbsp;into fine crumbs with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> (keep them in the bag so you don't lose them!).</p>\r\n<p>Chop the<strong> dill </strong>finely, including the stalks.</p>\r\n<p>Combine the<strong>&nbsp;c</strong><strong>hopped dill</strong>,<strong> bashed hazelnuts</strong>, <strong>lemon zest</strong>&nbsp;in a bowl. Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; this is your<strong> hazelnut&nbsp;crumb</strong>.</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
